# Build context is the repo root (combined frontend+backend image). The
# Dockerfile only ever COPYs from frontend/ and backend/, so use an allowlist:
# ignore everything, then re-include just those two trees. New top-level files
# or dirs are excluded by default and can't accidentally bloat or leak into the
# image.
#
# NOTE: .dockerignore is independent of .gitignore — Docker never consults git.
# Anything present on disk is sent to the build unless excluded HERE, so the
# junk patterns below must be spelled out even though git already ignores them.
*

# The only two trees the image build reads.
!frontend
!backend

# Deps and build/test artifacts — reinstalled/regenerated inside the image.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/dist-gdocs
**/tests
**/test-results
**/playwright-report

# Language/tool caches (gitignored, but Docker doesn't know that).
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.pytest_cache

# Secrets and local env files must never be baked into a layer.
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/.env-*

# Misc junk and dev-only tooling.
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log
**/.husky

# Backend runtime data must never be baked into the image (mounted at runtime).
backend/logs
backend/data
